### 6. [MODIFY] `app/OrderDetailScreen.tsx`

**2 changes made:**

#### 6a. State + Fetch (~line 89 and ~line 96)

```typescript
// New state
const [shipmentInfo, setShipmentInfo] = useState<{
  shipping_method_label: string;
  calculated_fee: number;
  estimated_days_text: string;
  origin_zone: string;
  destination_zone: string;
  tracking_number: string | null;
  status: string;
} | null>(null);

// Fetch on mount (added to existing useEffect)
supabase
  .from('order_shipments')
  .select('shipping_method_label, calculated_fee, estimated_days_text, origin_zone, destination_zone, tracking_number, status')
  .eq('order_id', realOrderId)
  .maybeSingle()
  .then(({ data }) => {
    if (data) setShipmentInfo(data);
  })
  .catch(() => { });
```

**Why `.maybeSingle()`:** Legacy orders placed before this feature won't have an `order_shipments` row. `.maybeSingle()` returns `null` instead of throwing.

#### 6b. Display Section (~line 631)

Renders between the "Recipient" address info and the "Courier Information" section:

```
┌─ Shipping & Delivery ────────────────────────────┐
│  Recipient: Juan Dela Cruz                        │ ← existing
│  +63 912 345 6789                                 │ ← existing
│  123 Main St, Makati, NCR                         │ ← existing
│                                                    │
│  ─────────────────────────────────────────────    │
│  Shipping Method                                   │ ← NEW (BX-09-003)
│  J&T Standard                                      │
│                                                    │
│  Estimated Delivery          Shipping Fee          │
│  3-5 days                    ₱135                  │
│                                                    │
│  NCR → Visayas                                     │ ← zone route
│                                                    │
│  ─────────────────────────────────────────────    │
│  Courier Information                               │ ← existing (shows after seller ships)
│  J&T Express     Tracking: JT123456789            │
│  Estimated: Apr 20, 2026                           │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Fallback:** If `shipmentInfo` is `null` (legacy order), the section simply doesn't render. No "unavailable" message needed — the courier tracking section already handles delivery info for orders that predate this feature.

---

## Data Flow — End to End

### During Checkout

```
1. Buyer selects/changes address
   └─▶ 300ms debounce fires
       └─▶ calculateShippingForSellers()
           └─▶ shippingResults[] updated (per seller: methods[], defaultMethod, zones)
               └─▶ ShippingMethodPicker renders per seller
               └─▶ Default method auto-selected in selectedMethods{}
               └─▶ perStoreShippingFees recomputed
               └─▶ grandTotal recomputed

2. Buyer taps alternative shipping method
   └─▶ onSelectMethod() → selectedMethods updated
       └─▶ perStoreShippingFees recomputed (instant, no debounce)
       └─▶ grandTotal recomputed
       └─▶ ShippingMethodPicker re-renders with new selection

3. Buyer taps "Place Order"
   └─▶ Guard 1: Address serviceable? ✓
   └─▶ Guard 2: Shipping still calculating? ✓
   └─▶ Guard 3: Any seller has error? ✓
   └─▶ Guard 4: Selected method still valid? ✓ (BX-09-002)
   └─▶ Build payload with shippingBreakdown[]
   └─▶ processCheckout()
       └─▶ For each seller:
           ├─▶ Create order
           ├─▶ Insert order_shipments row (fire-and-forget)
           ├─▶ Send buyer notification
           └─▶ Send seller notification
```

### After Order Placement

```
4. Buyer opens Order Detail screen
   └─▶ useEffect fetches from order_shipments table
       └─▶ shipmentInfo state populated
       └─▶ "Shipping Method" + "Estimated Delivery" + "Shipping Fee" section rendered

5. Seller ships the order (future — not in this sprint)
   └─▶ Seller updates order_shipments:
       ├─▶ tracking_number = 'JT123456789'
       ├─▶ status = 'shipped'
       └─▶ shipped_at = now()
```

---

## What's NOT Included (Out of Scope)

| Item | Why | Where It Belongs |
|---|---|---|
| Seller-side tracking number input | Seller flow, not buyer checkout | Separate seller story |
| Shipping status webhook from J&T | Integration story | API integration sprint |
| Method picker in seller's order detail | Read-only display for seller | Could be added to `seller/OrderDetailScreen.tsx` |
| Notification on shipping method change | Not in AC | Enhancement |
